  "notes": "v3 extends v2's training corpus to include panel-font digit samples (training_data_user_panel/0-9) on top of the signature-font samples (training_data_user_sig_rgb/0-9). Different SC ships render the signature scanner in different fonts depending on manufacturer, so v2 (sig font only) catastrophically misclassified panel-font digits \u2014 empirically panel '0' read as '7' at 0.89-0.97 confidence. Architecture is identical to v2 (3 conv blocks + FC, 3x28x28 input, 11 outputs); only the training corpus changes. Panel grayscale (L) is replicated to 3 RGB channels at load time. Per-class balance keeps panel:sig at >= 1:1 within each digit class so panel font is fully represented."
